{
  "number": 839,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/839",
  "title": "hierarchicalMenu: hide parent's siblings when a sub level is selected",
  "body": "For now when a item is selected in the hierarchicalMenu, if that one contains child elements then it displays those. But at the same time it also displays all the sibling elements of the parent level.\n\nHidden the parent's sibling items is a UX pattern that we can see on more and more website: Amazon, Birchbox.fr\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1101220/13044727/fc8e961c-d3cf-11e5-94d6-1365eb3e6f83.png)\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1101220/13044710/e5481fdc-d3cf-11e5-8b7d-acf260d4a784.png)\n\nCould be interesting providing that out of the box, as part of the hierarchicalMenu widget.\n\nPS: That behavior is already handled by the JS Helper https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js#hide-parent-level-of-current-parent-level\n",
